 
Donâ€™t Do Crime Act
Mayoral Legislation of Los Santos





Proposal : 



This Act will establish an update to the established penal code of Los Santos. This update is necessary to allow the LSPD to charge people according to the actions that an individual may have committed. 




Guidelines and Rules:



This Act will bring about change to the current penal code. All of the charges presented are viewable by the public and subject to Senate review and revocation. 

https://docs.google.com/document/d/1At7IyP9kqyPh-2f5rIIDKUvbO58ljIPWk_xCD20dRQ4/edit?usp=sharing








Reason for Legislation:



There has been an uptick in crime without charges and the City needs to stay on top of it. This should help the citizens of the city to feel safe in the place they live with a penal code that reflects the actions of others. 



Council Votes
Doug Bennet - Approval
Bobby Porter - Approval

